#8217;m guilty of all 8.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.strangerstudios.com/blog/2012/10/mistake-1-lack-of-goals/\">Mistake #1: Lack of Goals</a></p>\n<blockquote><p>\n<strong>What do you want people who visit your website to do?</strong><br />\n&#8230;<br />\nWhen asked what the goal of your website is, you might have answered 2-5 things. Great! Throw away items 2 through 5. What was your first answer? Do that. On your homepage.</p></blockquote>\n<p>The advice applies to all websites, but is fairly easy to parse for membership websites.</p>\n<p>Is the #1 goal of your website to sign up members? Better put a big fat sign up button right on your homepage. Maybe put the sign up form on your homepage.</p>\n<p>Do you have multiple membership levels? Maybe you should pick just one to focus on. Make it more prominent or make it the only option on the homepage.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"http://www.paidmembershipspro.com/2012/10/biggest-mistake-website-owners-make/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Update 1.5.2.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"http://www.paidmembershipspro.com/2012/09/update-1-5-2-1/\";